title: Staycation

text:
Sudah dua kali menginap di sini selama 2021. Yang pertama bersama teman kerja urusan pekerjaan, yang kedua bersama keluarga untuk menghabiskan akhir pekan. Semua pengalaman yang dirasakan semua menyenangkan.

Hotel bintang 4 rasa bintang 5. Kebetulan request kamar saya terpenuhi, jadi saya merasa senang. 
Proses check in cepat, semua staf sangat ramah dan helpful.

Ketika sudah masuk dalam kamar, keadaan sangat bersih. Begitu pula dengan kamar mandi. Perlengkapan mandi lengkap, tersedia hair dryer, handuk bersih (badan, muka, tangan). Namun sayangnya lantai di bagian shower kurang miring, sehingga setelah mandi sangat becek. Dan menurut saya lebih baik di wastafel dilengkapi hand soap.

Luas kamar lumayan lega, penerangan cukup baik, tv gambarnya jernih&channel bervariatif, wifi agak lambat, ac kamar dingin, kulkas kurang dingin (malah terasa panas karena tertutup bawah meja). Yang paling juara adalah : tempat tidur, bantal, selimut bersih, empuk, dan nyaman!

Karena tidak memesan kamar dengan sarapan, jadi saya tidak tahu bagaimana menu sarapan. Lebih baik berenang saat pagi2, di saat itulah kolam sepi. Keadaan kolam luas dan menyenangkan.

Terima kasih banyak The Manohara Hotel Yogyakarta!

text:
1. Bedroom: Booked Deluxe and Grand Deluxe. I was told by reception there is no connecting rooms between Deluxe Rooms. Connecting rooms only available between Deluxe and Grand Deluxe and that leads me to upgrade one Deluxe room to Grand Deluxe. The price of Grand Deluxe is twice the price of Deluxe room. For those who expect a connecting room in Manohara, they may want to take this into consideration as the price gap between both rooms are ridiculously huge. Deluxe room basically is large enough     and Grand Deluxe is slightly more spacious and bigger sofa. The cleanliness standard is top notch and the hotel itself has been running for at least a year. Pretty much a brand-new hotel by my standard

2. Bathroom: overall spacious, clean and well-maintained. The body soap and shampoo have a nice soothing scent. Nice amenities. Hot/cold water works properly.

3. Breakfast: Decent buffet spreads, mainly mainstream Indonesian and some choice of Western foods. 

4. Parking: hotel provides both indoor and outdoor parking but seems like only few limited spaces. Can’t imagine the high season or school holiday period.

5. Location: The hotel is quite at a reasonable distance to city centre and some places of interest

6. Overall: Spent Rp 560,000 per night for Deluxe and I have to add extra Rp 500,000 for the upgraded Grand Deluxe. Quite pricey given Deluxe room itself is fabulous already. If connecting rooms isn’t necessarily important part of your travel plan, this hotel is such a gem and value for money.
